<!-- ===== MATERIALS ===== -->
<section class="mat">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="head">
      <div>
        <div class="kicker sr"><i></i><span class="eyebrow">Materials &amp; Craft · 05</span></div>
        <h2 class="sr">An honest<br>palette of <em>things.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <p class="sr">We work with materials that age — that take on patina, soften with light, and improve over the years rather than degrade. A few we return to again and again.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card sr">
        <div class="ph"><img src="images/projects/10.jpeg" alt="Lime and earth" onerror="this.style.background='#E5DCCB'"></div>
        <div class="body">
          <div class="n">01 · Earth</div>
          <h3>Lime &amp; Plaster</h3>
          <p>Hand-troweled lime plasters and earth pigments that breathe with the seasons — cool to the touch, soft to the eye, kind to old walls.</p>
          <div class="row"><span>Origin · Local</span><span>Hand-applied</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card sr">
        <div class="ph"><img src="images/projects/ongoing/construction1.jpg" alt="Hardwood" onerror="this.style.background='#E5DCCB'"></div>
        <div class="body">
          <div class="n">02 · Wood</div>
          <h3>Ugandan Hardwood</h3>
          <p>Mvule, mahogany and musizi — milled, seasoned and joined by hand. Used for doors, louvres, beams and the long pieces of furniture we love.</p>
          <div class="row"><span>Origin · East Africa</span><span>Joinery</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card sr">
        <div class="ph"><img src="images/projects/ongoing/construction2.jpg" alt="Brass and stone" onerror="this.style.background='#E5DCCB'"></div>
        <div class="body">
          <div class="n">03 · Metal</div>
          <h3>Brass &amp; Stone</h3>
          <p>Hand-cast brass that ages to a soft brown, set against quartzite and basalt cut from quarries an hour from our studio.</p>
          <div class="row"><span>Origin · Workshop</span><span>Bespoke</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== PROCESS ===== -->
<section class="proc">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="head">
      <div class="kicker sr"><i style="background:var(--terra-soft)"></i><span class="eyebrow">How We Work · 06</span></div>
      <h2 class="sr">A patient,<br>four-step <em>method.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step sr">
        <div class="n">01</div>
        <h3>Listen &amp; Brief</h3>
        <p>We sit, we walk the site, we ask too many questions. The brief is written together — not handed down.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step sr">
        <div class="n">02</div>
        <h3>Sketch &amp; Concept</h3>
        <p>Hand-drawn plans, mood boards and a clear architectural intent — before any computer is opened.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step sr">
        <div class="n">03</div>
        <h3>Develop &amp; Visualise</h3>
        <p>Photo-real 3D walk-throughs, full material schedules and a fixed budget agreed in writing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step sr">
        <div class="n">04</div>
        <h3>Build &amp; Hand Over</h3>
        <p>Weekly site supervision, trusted Ugandan craftspeople, and a home — not a building — handed over.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== TESTIMONIALS ===== -->
<section class="tst">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="head">
      <div>
        <div class="kicker sr"><i></i><span class="eyebrow">Voices · 06</span></div>
        <h2 class="sr">In their <em>own words.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="nav-btns sr">
        <div class="count"><b id="tCur">01</b><s>/ 04</s></div>
        <div class="btns">
          <button id="prev" aria-label="Previous">←</button>
          <button id="next" aria-label="Next">→</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stage">
      <div class="ph">
        <div class="pi on"><img src="images/projects/muyoyo.jpeg" alt="" onerror="this.parentNode.style.background='#3a3833'"></div>
        <div class="pi"><img src="images/projects/3.jpeg" alt="" onerror="this.parentNode.style.background='#3a3833'"></div>
        <div class="pi"><img src="images/projects/7.jpeg" alt="" onerror="this.parentNode.style.background='#3a3833'"></div>
        <div class="pi"><img src="images/projects/6.jpeg" alt="" onerror="this.parentNode.style.background='#3a3833'"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="slider" id="slider">
        <div class="slide on">
          <div class="stars">★ ★ ★ ★ ★</div>
          <p class="q">LAPHIC didn't just design our home — they understood how we wanted to live in it. Three years later, every room still feels like the first day.</p>
          <div class="who"><div class="av">SM</div><div><div class="n">Sarah &amp; Mark</div><span class="r">Muyoyo Residence · 2022</span></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide">
          <div class="stars">★ ★ ★ ★ ★</div>
          <p class="q">The level of craft is the kind you usually only read about. Every joint, every tile, every line of mortar — considered.</p>
          <div class="who"><div class="av">DN</div><div><div class="n">David Nkurunziza</div><span class="r">Naguru House · 2023</span></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide">
          <div class="stars">★ ★ ★ ★ ★</div>
          <p class="q">They drew our garden with the same care as the house. We sit outside more than we sit in — that is everything.</p>
          <div class="who"><div class="av">AN</div><div><div class="n">Aisha &amp; Noel</div><span class="r">Kira Courtyard · 2024</span></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide">
          <div class="stars">★ ★ ★ ★ ★</div>
          <p class="q">Calm, professional, and quietly perfectionist. I would not build with anyone else in Uganda.</p>
          <div class="who"><div class="av">JK</div><div><div class="n">James Kakembo</div><span class="r">Bukoto Loft · 2024</span></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="strip" id="dots">
      <button class="dot on" data-i="0"><b>01</b> Muyoyo</button>
      <button class="dot" data-i="1"><b>02</b> Naguru</button>
      <button class="dot" data-i="2"><b>03</b> Kira</button>
      <button class="dot" data-i="3"><b>04</b> Bukoto</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== JOURNAL ===== -->
<section class="jrn">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="head">
      <div>
        <div class="kicker sr"><i></i><span class="eyebrow">From the Journal · 09</span></div>
        <h2 class="sr">Notes &amp; <em>inspirations.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="r sr">
        <a href="inspirations.html" class="btn ghost">All Stories <span class="arr">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <a class="post sr" href="inspirations.html">
        <div class="ph"><img src="images/projects/muyoyo.jpeg" alt="" onerror="this.style.background='#E5DCCB'"></div>
        <div class="meta"><span>Architecture</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>05 min read</span></div>
        <h3>Designing for Ugandan light: a year of east-west sketches.</h3>
        <p>Why the orientation of every line we draw begins with the sun, and how a few millimetres of shadow can change a whole room.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="post sr" href="inspirations.html">
        <div class="ph"><img src="images/projects/3.jpeg" alt="" onerror="this.style.background='#E5DCCB'"></div>
        <div class="meta"><span>Materials</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>07 min read</span></div>
        <h3>The slow case for lime: why we keep coming back to it.</h3>
        <p>A short field note on lime plasters — how they breathe, age, and quietly outlast every fashionable finish.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="post sr" href="inspirations.html">
        <div class="ph"><img src="images/projects/7.jpeg" alt="" onerror="this.style.background='#E5DCCB'"></div>
        <div class="meta"><span>Landscape</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>04 min read</span></div>
        <h3>A garden is a room: drawing outside as carefully as in.</h3>
        <p>How we plan the garden in the same drawing as the house — water, shade, scent and the slow season of bloom.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== FAQ ===== -->
<section class="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="left">
        <div class="kicker sr"><i></i><span class="eyebrow">Questions · 10</span></div>
        <h2 class="sr">A few things<br>worth <em>knowing.</em></h2>
        <p class="sr">The ones we're asked most. If your question isn't here, write to us — we read every message ourselves.</p>
        <a href="contact.html" class="btn dark sr">Ask Us Anything <span class="arr">→</span></a>
      </div>
      <div class="list" id="faq">
        <div class="q on"><div class="h"><h3>How long does a typical home take?</h3><span class="pl"></span></div><div class="a"><p>Design takes three to six months depending on size and complexity. Construction is typically twelve to eighteen months. We share a written timeline at the end of concept stage and keep to it.</p></div></div>
        <div class="q"><div class="h"><h3>Do you work outside Kampala?</h3><span class="pl"></span></div><div class="a"><p>Yes — we have completed projects on the Lake, in Mbarara, Jinja, Mbale and as far as Kigali. Site supervision outside Kampala is arranged with a local site architect we trust.</p></div></div>
        <div class="q"><div class="h"><h3>What's your minimum project size?</h3><span class="pl"></span></div><div class="a"><p>For full architecture, we focus on homes from around 200 m² upwards. For interiors and renovations, there is no minimum — we love small, careful projects.</p></div></div>
        <div class="q"><div class="h"><h3>Can you work with my existing builder?</h3><span class="pl"></span></div><div class="a"><p>Often, yes — we are happy to design and supervise while you run construction. We assess your builder's capacity during the tender stage and write the contract accordingly.</p></div></div>
        <div class="q"><div class="h"><h3>How are fees calculated?</h3><span class="pl"></span></div><div class="a"><p>Architectural fees are a percentage of construction value, typically eight to twelve per cent. Interior, landscape and 3D work are quoted as fixed fees. Every figure is in writing before we begin.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== CTA / CONTACT ===== -->
<section class="cta" id="contact">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2 class="sr">Have a site,<br>a sketch, a <em>dream?</em><br>Let's <em>begin.</em></h2>
    <div class="actions sr">
      <a href="contact.html" class="btn dark">Start a Project <span class="arr">→</span></a>
      <a href="https://wa.me/256705029291" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn ghost">WhatsApp Us <span class="arr">→</span></a>
    </div>
